career_highlights:
I'm passionate about helping more people create positive impact in the world through the power of entrepreneurship.

I'm a community builder, and get a kick out of creating value through connecting others. I am currently working on a new startup support community (Web3 DAO), consisting of values-aligned startup founders, operators, and startup community 'enablers' who collaborate to share our networks, our knowledge, and our know-how to help each other create more impact in the world, and capture that value for the long-term benefit of the community using Web3 as a platform.

As an EHF Fellow, I've been focussed mostly on building more sustainable innovation ecosystems in New Zealand:

* Innovating the future of high school entrepreneurial education in my prior role as CDO at Young Enterprise Trust;
* Investing in the future of mental health innovation in NZ through my current board role at Ember Innovations;
* Inspiring Government to create a more vibrant entrepreneurial economy in NZ by working towards 8 key ecosystem impact goals detailed in my work at StartNZUp.com;
* By designing NZ's Health Innovation Ecosystem Strategy for NZ's Ministry of Health - a transformational ecosystem platform for nurturing & supporting more innovation in the health sector; &
* Building a values-aligned Web3 community of change makers, startup founders, & ecosystem builders who are paying it forward via open knowledge, networks, and know-how to help more people have access to the resources they need to create more impact in the world.

My career has shaped my core values around giving back to the community, helping others, and a belief in the power of entrepreneurship in having personal impact in the world. I regularly write about these topics at https://medium.com/@dankhan & https://mirror.xyz/leancto.eth

